<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="92" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">
Zambia, Transvaal (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, CE" journalOrPublisher="Agricultural Research Service, USDA" pageId="52" pageNumber="101" refId="B51" refString="Smith, CE, 1971. Observations on Stengelioid species of Vernonia. In: Agriculture Handbook. Agricultural Research Service, USDA" title="Observations on Stengelioid species of Vernonia." volumeTitle="Agriculture Handbook." year="1971">Smith 1971</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="92" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">
The specimen cited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, CE" journalOrPublisher="Agricultural Research Service, USDA" pageId="52" pageNumber="101" refId="B51" refString="Smith, CE, 1971. Observations on Stengelioid species of Vernonia. In: Agriculture Handbook. Agricultural Research Service, USDA" title="Observations on Stengelioid species of Vernonia." volumeTitle="Agriculture Handbook." year="1971">Smith (1971)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oliv" authorityYear="1881" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia nyassae" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nyassae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Vernonia nyassae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Oliv. from Transvaal, is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Rob., Skvarla &amp; V. A. Funk" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="H. Rob., Skvarla &amp; V. A. Funk" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Pseudopegolettia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pseudopegolettia thodei" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thodei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Pseudopegolettia thodei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The two species have generally similar habits, but they are totally different entities with basically different pollen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">
It is evident from the description that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klatt" authorityYear="1896" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia collina" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="collina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Vernonia collina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Klatt, based on a Schlechter collection, is not the same as the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Klatt" authorityYear="1896" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia collina" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="collina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Vernonia collina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Schlechter. See under unplaced species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
